  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Girls Right to Pad Initiative</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Nigeria, sanitary pads costs an average of $1.30 per pack, while most families live below the poverty threshold of $1.20 per day. The high cost of sanitary pads in Nigeria have made them inaccessible for poor girls. In some situations, girls face sexual abuse in their quest for money to buy sanitary pads. During  menstruation  they are unable to attend school. On the other hand, those who cannot afford a good menstrual pad, rely on old rags and and tissue papers as alternatives.</narrative>
  </description>
